## Contributing

Thank you for your interest in contributing to {{PROJECT_NAME}}!

### Getting Started

- Review open issues or create a new one describing the problem or feature.
- Fork the repository and create a feature branch.
- Make your changes with clear commits and tests where applicable.
- Run local checks (linting, formatting, tests) before opening a pull request.

### Pull Requests

- Reference the issue the PR addresses.
- Provide screenshots or logs when changing user-facing behaviour.
- Ensure CI checks pass.
- Request review from the CODEOWNERS listed in `.github/CODEOWNERS`.

### Code of Conduct

This project adheres to the Contributor Covenant. By participating you agree to uphold this code. Please report unacceptable behaviour to {{CONTACT_EMAIL}}.
